The paper deals with the relationship between sample compression and statistical learning, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of logarithmic sample size and uniform convergence, which are concepts related to information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC), respectively. The paper also provides some applications of the compressibility-learnability equivalences, which could fall under the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
